channel.title: Cannot find symbol compile error?
channel.description:
So I'm trying to use this tut: Collection bag store more than 900 trillion gp: http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,551735.0.html
I've created the file "MoneyPouch.java" in the src/model/players folder, where Client.java is.
I was told in the tut to add this to Client.java:
[code] private MoneyPouch moneyPouch = new MoneyPouch(this); public MoneyPouch getPouch() { return moneyPouch; }[/code]
But the compiler tells me: [code]src\server\model\players\Client.java:40: error: cannot find symbol import server.model.players.MoneyPouch; ^ symbol: class MoneyPouch location: package server.model.players src\server\model\players\Client.java:49: error: cannot find symbol private MoneyPouch moneyPouch = new MoneyPouch(this); ^ symbol: class MoneyPouch location: class Client src\server\model\players\Client.java:50: error: cannot find symbol public MoneyPouch getPouch() { ^ symbol: class MoneyPouch location: class Client src\server\model\players\Client.java:49: error: cannot find symbol private MoneyPouch moneyPouch = new MoneyPouch(this); ^ symbol: class MoneyPouch location: class Client [/code]
Any idea why? I've tried to put this in client.java also: [code]import server.model.players.MoneyPouch;[/code]
I can't seem to figure out the problem :\
Any help is greatly appreciated!
